1
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:57,474
ALL CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS,
PLACES AND EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL.

2
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,376
It’s a bomb! I found an explosive!

3
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:31,758
Please evacuate! It’s a bomb!

4
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:34,761
Please back away! A bomb has been found!

5
00:01:34,886 --> 00:01:37,138
-Please evacuate!
-Evacuate the area!

6
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:38,890
-This way.
-Please evacuate.

7
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,351
-Please evacuate!
-Evacuate the area!

8
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:45,814
We fear there might be a second explosion.
Yes, sir.

9
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:53,822
Based on Article 26, Paragraph 1
of the Government Organization Act,

10
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,573
you have been entrusted

11
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:59,661
with all the authority and duties of
the President of the Republic of Korea.

12
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:01,871
Pardon?

13
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:05,542
From this moment forward,
you are now the acting president.

14
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:08,086
Your term has already begun,
President Park.

15
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:28,481
It's a claymore.

16
00:02:45,456 --> 00:02:48,418
What? It looks like a standard claymore
on the outside,

17
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:50,628
but it's not a simple claymore.

18
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:55,133
It's a type of explosive often spotted
in terrorist attacks in Algeria and Syria.

19
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:59,596
Everyone’s waiting for you.

20
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:06,686
We have no time to talk about
what measures we should take right now!

21
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:10,106
We’re at war right now!
Do you not know what that means?

22
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:20,575
CURRENT STATUS OF YEOUIDO

23
00:03:20,658 --> 00:03:22,577
SITE OF INCIDENT

24
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,014
We shouldn’t react emotionally.

25
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,058
We need to figure out what happened first.

26
00:03:45,266 --> 00:03:47,727
It’s too soon to call it a war
and make rash judgments.

27
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,646
And who will make that decision?

28
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,522
Our commander-in-chief isn't here.

29
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:55,151
I will now deactivate the explosive.

30
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:27,600
This is the NSC,
the National Security Council.

31
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,979
The final decisions on matters
of national security,

32
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:32,981
unification, and diplomacy are made here.

33
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:34,983
You, sir, the acting president,

34
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:36,859
are the current chief of the NSC.

35
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:40,780
If a war breaks out on the Korean
Peninsula now, it'll be World War III!

36
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:43,574
Even if it means World War IV,
we must do what we must do!

37
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:45,743
-That's irresponsible!
-Should we sit back and watch?

38
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:48,371
-You can't be so emotional--
-The acting president is here!

39
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,039
We must think about our people!

40
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,417
Being bullheaded isn't a solution.

41
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,585
Whom are you calling bullheaded?

42
00:04:59,924 --> 00:05:00,925
Sir.

43
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:04,053
This is Acting President Park Mu-jin.

44
00:05:43,801 --> 00:05:47,597
DAY 60: COMMANDER-IN-CHIEF
EPISODE 2

45
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:09,619
The bomb has been deactivated.

46
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:25,301
We believe the bombers used
an explosive demolition technique

47
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:28,179
to blow up the National Assembly Building.

48
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:30,098
-"Explosive demolition"?
-That's correct.

49
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:34,519
You place the explosives
on the pillars or the walls in advance.

50
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,816
Using the weight of the building itself,

51
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:44,779
the explosives are detonated.

52
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:50,159
In 5 to 15 seconds, these explosives
can destroy large buildings.

53
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:54,205
Most importantly, a relatively
small amount of explosives is sufficient.

54
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:57,208
-It could've been difficult to spot--
-Next.

55
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,503
Therefore, the amount of explosives
used was--

56
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:02,422
Enough with that. Next.

57
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:03,840
Sir?

58
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:06,050
Tell me the most crucial
piece of information.

59
00:07:07,009 --> 00:07:08,719
Don't you know what I want to know?

60
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,639
So? Was it North Korea or not?

61
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,891
We're not sure about that yet, sir.

62
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:18,312
If it was, the military will take over.
If it wasn't, it'll go to the police.

63
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,857
Shouldn't this be your number one focus?

64
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:25,111
Wow, our deputy commissioner general
is very straightforward.

65
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:26,946
You're no-nonsense.

66
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:31,576
The president, prime minister,
ministers, and assemblymen,

67
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:33,786
over 100 high-ranking
government officials,

68
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:36,080
lost their lives at the same time
in an attack.

69
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,916
Is this the right time to discuss
jurisdictions?

70
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:40,751
You're right.

71
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,963
Over 100 high-ranking
government officials were massacred.

72
00:07:44,046 --> 00:07:47,341
And in the center of Seoul,
the nation's capital.

73
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:51,804
The people will probably question
who did this.

74
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:55,516
And they'll wonder
who will take responsibility for this.

75
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:58,352
Do you know why? Because they're anxious.

76
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:03,983
The commissioner general needs something
to say to the people to save face.

77
00:08:06,402 --> 00:08:09,322
You. Did you say
that you're from the Terrorism Task Force?

78
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,699
What's your take on this?

79
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,994
Who did it?

80
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:19,415
Who planted these explosives
in the National Assembly Building?

81
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,798
They're explosives used
in prior terrorist attacks.

82
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:31,552
They're the same explosives North Korea
has been exporting to its allies.

83
00:08:35,014 --> 00:08:36,098
It's them.

84
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:40,853
Are they seriously trying to start a war?

85
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:44,524
They want to start a war!

86
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:47,360
This isn't a terrorist attack!
This is a declaration of war!

87
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:48,653
This is a preemptive attack!

88
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:50,196
"A declaration of war"?

89
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:53,157
Look. No movements have been spotted
in their camps.

90
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,785
All their missile launchers are in place.

91
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,954
Does it seem like
they're preparing for a war?

92
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,874
North Korea has made an announcement.

93
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:05,711
Here.

94
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:08,464
A disaster has occurred in South Korea

95
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,883
with the destruction
of its National Assembly Building.

96
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:13,010
The US and the hostile forces

97
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:16,931
are planning something wicked by

98
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:19,392
pointing their fingers at North Korea.

99
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:21,269
Such a scheme...

100
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:24,605
They're strongly asserting
that they have nothing to do with this.

101
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:27,608
This is the first time
they responded immediately

102
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:29,860
to the public sentiment in South Korea.

103
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:32,405
They were about to establish
diplomatic relations with us.

104
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:36,242
They're determined to be acknowledged
as a "normal" country.

105
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:37,618
Didn't you hear them?

106
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,704
They were preparing for the peace treaty.

107
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:42,748
Think about this logically.

108
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:44,917
"Logically"? My logic tells me

109
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,211
that a mad dog should be beaten

110
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,714
and that provocation should be punished.

111
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:50,965
"'Normal' country," you say?

112
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:54,176
North Korea is finally showing
their true colors.

113
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:56,095
Since the US isn't listening to them,

114
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:57,763
they used us as a sacrificial lamb!

115
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,016
They're saying, "Look!
We can do anything!"

116
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,893
We need to make a decision!

117
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,729
We should attack
the Kumsusan Palace of the Sun

118
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,397
or cross the demarcation line!

119
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,983
Better yet, we must destroy
their nuclear facilities.

120
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:12,820
That way, they won't be able
to start a war with us

121
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:14,405
since we're stronger than they are!

122
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:16,449
Is it even possible
to make such a decision?

123
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:19,619
Whether it be attacking the Kumsusan
Palace or crossing the demarcation line,

124
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:21,912
we do not have wartime control.

125
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,708
Our country is protected

126
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:29,920
by its alliance with the US.

127
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:34,592
It's a pride of our military.

128
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:38,095
If we don't show our determination
and will to fight immediately

129
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:42,183
and the power of our military,
which is stronger than North Korea's,

130
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:45,770
we may be subjected to
an even bigger attack.

131
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:49,023
During the September 11 attacks,

132
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:52,109
the terrorists' second target
was the Pentagon.

133
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,111
Did you all forget that?

134
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:59,617
Request the ROK-US Combined Forces
Command to declare DEFCON 3.

135
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:05,247
Furthermore, our military should prepare
for combat.

136
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:09,669
Are you insisting on waging a war
on the Korean Peninsula?

137
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,337
It's very reckless to conclude

138
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,839
North Korea was responsible
based on one bomb that was found!

139
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,299
Then who was it?

140
00:11:16,092 --> 00:11:17,927
We are a divided country.

141
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:20,179
Our main adversary is situated
right above us.

142
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,722
If it wasn't them, then who was it?

143
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:24,767
Will you only believe it

144
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:27,269
if it reads "Made in North Korea"
on the explosives?

145
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:30,064
North Korea? Does that even make sense?

146
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:34,026
Hold on. How could you
defend them in this situation?

147
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:36,112
Something must be wrong with the NSC!

148
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,863
What did you say? Are you done?

149
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:40,533
-Then how am I to understand...
-Come on.

150
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,326
-...your reaction?
-How could you say that?

151
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,869
Did I say something wrong?

152
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:45,996
Then should we just sit still and take it?

153
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,416
-Think about our people!
-I explained the situation.

154
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,876
Why are you being so pigheaded?

155
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,712
-What are you afraid of?
-Our security

156
00:11:52,795 --> 00:11:55,923
and the lives of our people are at risk!
I'm just asking you to be more careful!

157
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,534
You can chew with your gums
if you have no teeth, and

158
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,828
the acting president can fill in
if there's no president,

159
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:27,747
but if you have no toilet paper,

160
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,373
you're in trouble.

161
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:35,671
You went through so much today.

162
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:37,757
You should be happy.

163
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,968
Starting tomorrow,
we'll have an acting president.

164
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,190
It wasn't just
the National Assembly Building.

165
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:55,816
The Blue House was hit with a bomb too.

166
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:03,324
That acting president's nickname
was Cinderella. It's obvious.

167
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:06,619
He probably brown-nosed politicians
and became a minister through nepotism.

168
00:13:06,702 --> 00:13:09,622
Just because he was lucky enough
to survive this attack,

169
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:12,124
he's become the head honcho of Korea.

170
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:16,837
He has only six months
of experience in politics,

171
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:19,089
and all he did was
measure fine dust levels.

172
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:21,217
What could he possibly do
against North Korea?

173
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,011
Actually, I'm scared
he might do something. Don't you agree?

174
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:39,985
Everyone says that you're so lucky.

175
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:47,785
The point I'm trying to make

176
00:13:47,868 --> 00:13:51,831
is that you're very lucky
when it comes to your career.

177
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:07,847
I'm sorry, sir.

178
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:11,892
To be frank, I was a bit concerned
after reading your resume.

179
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:13,018
I apologize.

180
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:15,187
No.

181
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:19,942
You simply made a quick judgment
with the given data.

182
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,862
It's an understandable survival instinct.

183
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:27,283
After all, this is an emergency situation.

184
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:33,247
I'll be waiting for your call.

185
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:34,874
Excuse me.

186
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:38,544
Is the chief presidential secretary
still in there?

187
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:45,301
What happens if I step down
as acting president?

188
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:48,846
I'm unqualified.

189
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:51,056
Look.

190
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:55,603
If you're talking about competence,

191
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:58,647
there was only one person
who was qualified.

192
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:00,608
And today,

193
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:03,110
we lost him.

194
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:04,320
But...

195
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:08,657
-I'm sure you know as well.
-Is this because of what happened today?

196
00:15:14,663 --> 00:15:17,541
Your termination had no legal effect.

197
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,335
MINISTER
PARK MU-JIN

198
00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:21,462
There was no time to process it.

199
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:26,258
But if you resign,

200
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,595
your current position will be vacant.

201
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:35,476
The only individuals who can succeed
are ministers and cabinet members.

202
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:42,775
Who could've ever imagined
that such a disaster would occur?

203
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:43,776
Then

204
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:46,028
what happens after I resign?

205
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:49,448
Authority

206
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:51,951
does not permit vacancy.

207
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:56,205
The clearest and obvious power

208
00:15:56,789 --> 00:15:58,666
will take control.

209
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:07,800
PAST PRESIDENTS

210
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:17,601
-Are you talking about a military coup?
-We've experienced such coups

211
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,105
several times in the past.

212
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:23,357
Sir.

213
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:25,818
We have a problem.

214
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,199
That's a Sawagiri vessel.

215
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:35,035
It's Japan's Self-Defense Forces'
Aegis destroyer.

216
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:39,623
Japan seems to have concluded
that a war is imminent.

217
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:41,625
But still.

218
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:44,294
How dare they trespass
into our waters without informing us?

219
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:46,046
It's a good opportunity for them.

220
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:49,008
Prime Minister Aso's approval rating
hit rock-bottom after the scandal.

221
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:51,510
It's good for them if we have problems.

222
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:53,971
Even better if their Self-Defense Forces
can intervene.

223
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,931
Leadership during a national crisis.

224
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,100
We've done that before as well.

225
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,811
This is because they have no respect
for our military.

226
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:02,312
It's obvious.

227
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:05,607
Japan has provoked us, and yet,
we're just watching.

228
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:07,818
Does that make sense?

229
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,029
We cannot prevent a war

230
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:12,489
unless we're prepared to fight one.

231
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:17,161
But our acting president doesn't
even realize something that simple.

232
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:23,333
Our nation pretty much doesn't have
a commander-in-chief right now.

233
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:29,631
There will be
no commander-in-chief either,

234
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,258
if you resign right now.

235
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,470
Mr. Secretary.

236
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:37,639
You should talk
with the Japanese ambassador.

237
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:40,350
If we don't solve this vessel issue
by daybreak,

238
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,770
things will get more complicated.

239
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:45,439
Their Self-Defense Forces
pretty much announced

240
00:17:45,522 --> 00:17:47,274
that a war is imminent.

241
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:50,402
When morning comes, the stock markets
will be shaken up.

242
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:53,697
The foreigners in this country will look
for tickets to go back home.

243
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:56,033
If that happens, we won't be able
to calm the people down.

244
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:57,993
We're running out of time, sir.

245
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:01,622
Do you still think

246
00:18:02,873 --> 00:18:04,291
you're unqualified?

247
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:10,380
I'm not asking you to exercise
presidential powers.

248
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,716
I'm asking you to perform
your duty as a citizen.

249
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:16,762
You were chosen as the acting president

250
00:18:17,387 --> 00:18:18,388
based on...

251
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:21,475
this country's constitution.

252
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:32,611
Aren't you tired?

253
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:33,987
