I have Si-jin’s hair tie.

327
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:53,306
She’ll look for it when she wakes up.

328
00:23:54,141 --> 00:23:56,810
Tell her I’ll give it to her
when she comes to me,

329
00:23:57,853 --> 00:23:59,771
so she should wake up soon and hurry over.

330
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:03,984
Si-jin will be fine.

331
00:24:06,361 --> 00:24:08,155
I’ll worry about her.

332
00:24:09,614 --> 00:24:13,034
You have so many other things
to worry about now.

333
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:19,166
We won’t be able to go home for a while.

334
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:22,169
I’m sorry I put you through this.

335
00:24:23,712 --> 00:24:26,339
Do you really think I mind?

336
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:30,677
You...

337
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:35,307
You could have been there
when it happened.

338
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:39,311
At least...

339
00:24:41,646 --> 00:24:42,981
we're still together.

340
00:24:51,281 --> 00:24:52,282
Is it true

341
00:24:53,283 --> 00:24:55,118
that a North Korean submarine vanished?

342
00:25:07,756 --> 00:25:09,549
A North-Korean Romeo-class

343
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:11,885
submarine left from Shinpo Base
and didn't return.

344
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:16,598
It’s a submarine built to
transport nuclear warheads.

345
00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:20,644
They advertised how it demonstrates
their top-class technology.

346
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:32,948
Do you understand now

347
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:36,284
why Japan dispatched the Aegis
to the East Sea?

348
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,787
...why Japan dispatched
the Aegis to the East Sea?

349
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:41,206
You should have discussed it
with our government first

350
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:44,167
if Japan is our ally.

351
00:25:44,251 --> 00:25:46,378
Are you concerned about Korea Passing?

352
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:49,381
Are you concerned about Korea Passing?

353
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:52,384
South Korea has failed
to protect its own president.

354
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:55,554
Why would Japan discuss

355
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:58,056
national security with such a nation?

356
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,184
South Korea has failed
to protect its own president.

357
00:26:01,518 --> 00:26:04,521
Why would Japan discuss
national security with such a nation?

358
00:26:04,604 --> 00:26:06,356
Are you kidding--

359
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,278
Let him speak.

360
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,711
Do you mean

361
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,589
you will join us as we prepare for war?

362
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:53,987
Where’s President Park now?

363
00:26:54,237 --> 00:26:56,156
Must we really consent to DEFCON 2?

364
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:59,159
If it’s true that North Korea’s sub
has moved south, yes.

365
00:26:59,242 --> 00:27:00,660
This is crazy.

366
00:27:01,244 --> 00:27:04,039
This is exactly
what the American hard-liners wanted.

367
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:05,332
Just think about it.

368
00:27:05,415 --> 00:27:08,293
To President Reynold, a provocation
from the North is a disaster.

369
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:10,086
His re-election is coming up soon.

370
00:27:10,795 --> 00:27:12,964
I bet he’ll choose
the most aggressive military action

371
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:15,550
to show that they won’t be
strong-armed by North Korea.

372
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,469
It’ll be more than
what the hard-liners wanted.

373
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:20,430
A DEFCON was declared
only twice in Korean history.

374
00:27:21,056 --> 00:27:22,974
The Panmunjeom axe murder incident in 1976

375
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:24,768
and the Rangoon bombing in 1983.

376
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:27,479
The US Army had to control the situation

377
00:27:27,562 --> 00:27:29,314
in case Korean soldiers retaliated.

378
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:31,107
At levels over DEFCON 3,

379
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:33,818
the operation authority goes
to the Combined Forces Command.

380
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:35,278
And it’s the same now.

381
00:27:35,362 --> 00:27:38,198
The US just wants
to have control over Korea.

382
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:41,368
It's too dangerous when there is tension
between the North and South like now.

383
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:43,119
Is the hotline still silent?

384
00:27:46,748 --> 00:27:47,874
We can't seem to reach them.

385
00:27:47,957 --> 00:27:51,336
There’s no response to the fax
we sent about the hotline either.

386
00:27:51,419 --> 00:27:53,797
It’s the same situation
with the military communications line.

387
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:56,758
They’re not sending or receiving
any transmissions, both land and maritime.

388
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,677
This is obviously a refusal to talk.

389
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:01,888
They’re like teenagers, locking
their door whenever something happens.

390
00:28:01,971 --> 00:28:05,016
If it’s true that
the submarine moved south,

391
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:07,686
then it could already be in front
of Jinhae Naval Base by now.

392
00:28:07,769 --> 00:28:09,020
We can’t make hasty conclusions.

393
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:11,815
From the North’s point of view,
stationing the Japanese Aegis

394
00:28:11,898 --> 00:28:15,443
is a provocation by the South
Korea-US-Japan alliance. For the North,

395
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:18,613
refusing to communicate
is the strongest option for protesting.

396
00:28:20,281 --> 00:28:23,410
June 1996, vice-ministerial level talks
between the two Koreas

397
00:28:23,493 --> 00:28:24,327
and...

398
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:28,289
the first battle at Baengnyeong.

399
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:33,253
June 2010, the Inter-Korean Summit

400
00:28:34,295 --> 00:28:35,714
and the Asan warship explosion.

401
00:28:36,923 --> 00:28:38,425
March 2012,

402
00:28:39,342 --> 00:28:41,219
an Inter-Korea Summit Agreement,

403
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:44,472
and the second battle
at Baengnyeong broke out.

404
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:45,515
And today,

405
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:48,601
March 4th, 2019,

406
00:28:49,352 --> 00:28:51,187
the National Assembly Building,

407
00:28:52,188 --> 00:28:57,652
the assassination of the president
and government officials.

408
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:01,614
Don’t you get it?

409
00:29:02,782 --> 00:29:05,785
North Korea has always mocked
the government’s Sunshine Policy.

410
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:08,204
And always with the same method.

411
00:29:09,456 --> 00:29:10,999
Do you still want to believe

412
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:14,377
-that they’re capable of communication?
-We don’t just believe it.

413
00:29:16,713 --> 00:29:17,714
We know it.

414
00:29:18,798 --> 00:29:20,717
We know that they need rice

415
00:29:21,968 --> 00:29:23,887
as much as we need peace.

416
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:28,808
Peace isn’t something
you beg for with money.

417
00:29:29,726 --> 00:29:32,937
It’s something you protect
with your blood.

418
00:29:35,398 --> 00:29:38,151
Your amateurish concept of security
and your fantasy of reunification

419
00:29:38,234 --> 00:29:39,652
cost you your boss.

420
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:41,196
And our military

421
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:44,073
lost our commander-in-chief.

422
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:02,008
We don’t have time, President Park.

423
00:30:02,091 --> 00:30:04,469
Give your consent to announce DEFCON 2.

424
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:08,264
DEFCON 2...

425
00:30:10,558 --> 00:30:14,145
Are you saying you’re certain
that North Korea is preparing for war?

426
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:17,774
Do you think any enemy
will ever let you know for certain?

427
00:30:19,192 --> 00:30:20,568
If we fear the North,

428
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:23,154
it’s not because of their nukes
or their missiles.

429
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:30,119
It means we can never know them.

430
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:32,705
Just like the submarine.

431
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:51,474
You got information
on the submarine, right?

432
00:30:51,558 --> 00:30:53,726
So what are the facts? Did it move south?

433
00:30:53,810 --> 00:30:56,646
Is it provocation? Just a drill?
Or is it--

434
00:30:56,729 --> 00:30:58,648
That won't make any difference.

435
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:00,441
Pardon?

436
00:31:01,651 --> 00:31:04,404
Do you know
why the government is like this today?

437
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:06,865
Well...

438
00:31:07,448 --> 00:31:10,702
It’s because the arrogant president
made our military

439
00:31:10,785 --> 00:31:14,414
and your intelligence service powerless
for the sake of peace.

440
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:18,084
I will never go back to those days.

441
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:20,628
Don't you agree?

442
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:26,175
I'm against this.

443
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:30,555
The moment President Park
consents to DEFCON 2,

444
00:31:30,972 --> 00:31:34,893
the leadership of this nation will go over
to the military and intelligence

445
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:36,978
since it means
we’re in a quasi-state of war.

446
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:40,648
Then regaining that power
will be impossible, sir.

447
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:44,903
You really are young.

448
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:49,324
You have the strength
to think about the future.

449
00:32:00,627 --> 00:32:02,795
You should’ve gone to the hospital
or taken a sick leave.

450
00:32:02,879 --> 00:32:04,380
It’s not too late.

451
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:18,645
Do you really think
I could go to the hospital?

452
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:21,981
That would be shameless of me.

453
00:32:24,776 --> 00:32:28,571
This is so unfair. I can't stand it.

454
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:33,952
Every step of the way for the past
two years to reach the peace treaty

455
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:36,996
has been difficult.

456
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:40,041
We had to worry about upsetting the US.

457
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:42,752
and pacifying the brazen North.

458
00:32:45,755 --> 00:32:48,174
We never got to eat peacefully
with our families

459
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:50,510
or take a vacation.

460
00:32:51,511 --> 00:32:53,680
We worked so hard to get this far.

461
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:57,517
How could it all go up in smoke like this?

462
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:58,935
We still...

463
00:33:00,937 --> 00:33:01,938
have time.

464
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:07,652
We’ll have to check the situation up north
as soon as possible.

465
00:33:07,902 --> 00:33:10,321
Whether we use the intelligence from China

466
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:12,156
or from third countries...

467
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:13,116
Mr. Ko.

468
00:33:14,701 --> 00:33:16,786
Can you connect me directly

469
00:33:17,453 --> 00:33:19,622
without going through NIS?

470
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:22,792
All right, sir.

471
00:33:22,875 --> 00:33:24,961
Contact the Chunchugwan
and issue a press embargo.

472
00:33:26,170 --> 00:33:28,631
Once the citizens start panicking,

473
00:33:29,507 --> 00:33:32,802
we may not have any other choice.

474
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:36,931
Let's just...

475
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:40,518
think about one thing for now.

476
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:43,813
Peace on the Korean Peninsula...

477
00:33:46,357 --> 00:33:48,568
was the president’s last unfinished work.

478
00:33:51,279 --> 00:33:52,613
The submarine, sir.

479
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:55,908
Do you really think
North Korea is preparing for an attack?

480
