of 15 knots...

487
00:34:16,763 --> 00:34:18,473
It's been nine days, so...

488
00:34:20,391 --> 00:34:22,602
How did they get
oxygen inside the submarine?

489
00:34:22,977 --> 00:34:25,938
They would have vaporized
liquid oxygen, right?

490
00:34:26,022 --> 00:34:27,231
Yes.

491
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:34,363
If it’s a diesel engine,
then they’d use lithium batteries.

492
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:36,449
What do you think?

493
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:39,118
Well...

494
00:34:40,078 --> 00:34:41,954
-Sir.
-Yes?

495
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:45,500
I... studied liberal arts.

496
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:49,629
Oh, I see.

497
00:34:52,381 --> 00:34:54,509
Is it that hard to understand?

498
00:34:54,967 --> 00:34:56,719
It’s North Korea we're talking about.

499
00:34:58,387 --> 00:34:59,931
Even if they're starving,

500
00:35:00,014 --> 00:35:01,766
they'll commandeer all the fishing boats

501
00:35:01,849 --> 00:35:03,726
to build submarines.

502
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:05,895
Why are you talking about college majors?

503
00:35:05,978 --> 00:35:07,230
What did you just say?

504
00:35:09,482 --> 00:35:10,817
I was talking to Mr. Park.

505
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:12,819
No, the fishing boats.

506
00:35:13,402 --> 00:35:15,404
You said they commandeered
all the fishing boats.

507
00:35:15,988 --> 00:35:18,991
Well, it's obvious.
Why else would there be no fishing boats

508
00:35:19,075 --> 00:35:20,368
when it’s halfbeak season?

509
00:35:20,451 --> 00:35:22,245
Are you sure? Do you have proof?

510
00:35:22,328 --> 00:35:23,621
Is that data reliable?

