00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:41,283
You're the one that said

777
00:52:41,366 --> 00:52:43,368
the bomb found at the site
was made in North Korea.

778
00:52:43,952 --> 00:52:45,162
It was a dud.

779
00:52:46,246 --> 00:52:50,292
What if someone orchestrated it
to make us...

780
00:52:53,044 --> 00:52:54,337
suspect North Korea?

781
00:52:59,843 --> 00:53:01,136
Who would do that?

782
00:53:06,099 --> 00:53:08,059
Do you approve of DEFCON 2?

783
00:53:08,185 --> 00:53:10,020
What happens after that?

784
00:53:19,237 --> 00:53:21,114
NORTH KOREA'S MAIN NUCLEAR FACILITIES

785
00:53:21,198 --> 00:53:23,116
It's called the Bloody Nose Strategy.

786
00:53:24,242 --> 00:53:28,455
It is a restricted and precise
preemptive strike

787
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:31,333
to display superior military strength

788
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:33,293
and intimidate them.

789
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:35,212
NORTH KOREA BOMBING SIMULATION

790
00:53:53,146 --> 00:53:55,774
As commander-in-chief
of the ROK military...

791
00:53:58,985 --> 00:54:02,239
SINUIJU, PYONGYANG,
PREDICTED LOCATION

792
00:54:11,122 --> 00:54:12,666
-Sir?
-It's strange.

793
00:54:14,376 --> 00:54:17,462
The submarine moved south,
but instead of defending our seas,

794
00:54:17,545 --> 00:54:19,798
we're hitting North Korea's
nuclear facilities first?

795
00:54:22,008 --> 00:54:23,927
We're incapacitating
their nuclear facilities,

796
00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:26,346
so North Korea cannot provoke us again.

797
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:29,224
It's just one of the options.

798
00:54:31,851 --> 00:54:34,479
It won't affect the South.

799
00:54:36,189 --> 00:54:38,066
If they are capable
of thinking reasonably,

800
00:54:38,149 --> 00:54:40,110
they won't start a full-scale war

801
00:54:41,069 --> 00:54:43,280
against the US.

802
00:54:46,116 --> 00:54:47,617
So, you're saying

803
00:54:47,701 --> 00:54:50,203
this will only be successful
under the assumption

804
00:54:50,287 --> 00:54:52,289
that North Korea
is reasonable and rational.

805
00:54:55,292 --> 00:54:57,460
Does North Korea seem like such a country

806
00:54:58,878 --> 00:54:59,713
to you, General Lee?

807
00:55:13,226 --> 00:55:14,853
Approve to increase to DEFCON 2.

808
00:55:15,770 --> 00:55:16,980
The North Korean submarine

809
00:55:18,023 --> 00:55:19,941
may not have infiltrated our waters.

810
00:55:20,025 --> 00:55:21,401
-Wait--
-We learned that the

811
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:24,779
marine ecosystem along the submarine
routes has been polluted by lithium.

812
00:55:24,863 --> 00:55:28,658
It is highly likely they drifted south
due to faulty batteries.

813
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:33,997
Can you prove that?

814
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:36,916
How could anyone prove that?

815
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:38,835
How would you prove it

816
00:55:38,918 --> 00:55:41,046
when it isn't caught on satellites
or sonars?

817
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:43,381
Unless North Korea admits it,

818
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:44,883
we won't be able to prove it.

819
00:55:49,929 --> 00:55:52,640
Then we have no choice.

820
00:55:55,268 --> 00:55:57,020
North Korea will have to confirm it.

821
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:11,659
You're defying Washington.

822
00:56:15,580 --> 00:56:18,041
You have put the Korean-US alliance
at risk because of a guess.

823
00:56:21,795 --> 00:56:23,129
It's my duty to report...

824
00:56:26,299 --> 00:56:27,967
We will abide by
President Reynold's decision.

825
00:56:39,354 --> 00:56:40,313
Tell him this.

826
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:42,774
Don't leave a single word out.

827
00:56:43,983 --> 00:56:45,485
The acting president

828
00:56:45,568 --> 00:56:49,239
is carrying out his job well
as commander-in-chief of the ROK.

829
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:51,866
We have operational authority
in times of peace.

830
00:57:01,459 --> 00:57:03,128
The moment you go through that door,

831
00:57:03,503 --> 00:57:05,755
you'll be the only one doubting

832
00:57:06,548 --> 00:57:08,174
the Korea-US alliance.

833
00:57:42,375 --> 00:57:44,252
Sir.

834
00:57:45,753 --> 00:57:49,090
North Korea has shut down
all communication channels.

835
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:51,634
You know they haven't responded

836
00:57:51,718 --> 00:57:54,220
to not only the communication lines,
but also the hotline.

837
00:57:58,683 --> 00:58:00,560
Why did they shut off the hotline

838
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:04,772
if the submarine really sank?

839
00:58:04,856 --> 00:58:07,650
They may be poor,
but they have self-respect.

840
00:58:08,610 --> 00:58:10,737
North Korea has been able
to last this long

841
00:58:10,820 --> 00:58:12,947
because of their pride
in independent national defense

842
00:58:13,031 --> 00:58:15,200
like nuclear or war arms technology.

843
00:58:18,703 --> 00:58:22,040
They probably don't want
the whole world to know

844
00:58:22,123 --> 00:58:25,877
the submarine the VIP is most proud of
sank due to a defect,

845
00:58:25,960 --> 00:58:27,545
especially not South Korea and the US.

846
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:30,173
Then there is nothing we can do.

847
00:58:30,256 --> 00:58:33,134
North Korea won't suddenly
swallow their pride and admit it.

848
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:42,101
THE DEMOCRATIC PEOPLE'S REPUBLIC OF KOREA
REPUBLIC OF KOREA, BLUE HOUSE

849
00:58:42,602 --> 00:58:43,728
Sir.

850
00:58:45,813 --> 00:58:48,900
Didn't you say there was
a defect in the submarine?

851
00:58:51,194 --> 00:58:54,572
Then why did you tell North Korea
it is drifting after hitting a rock?

852
00:58:57,909 --> 00:58:59,077
Someone told me...

853
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:01,871
that they may be poor,

854
00:59:02,539 --> 00:59:04,332
but that doesn't mean
they don't have self-respect.

855
00:59:07,794 --> 00:59:09,045
Now,

856
00:59:09,712 --> 00:59:11,506
do we just have to wait

857
00:59:12,173 --> 00:59:14,259
for North Korea to reply
through the hotline?

858
00:59:15,927 --> 00:59:18,805
"After communicating through fax or phone,

859
00:59:18,888 --> 00:59:22,433
we are to reply through a direct call
between the leaders within 10 minutes."

860
00:59:24,143 --> 00:59:26,646
That's the rule of operation
of the hotline set by both Koreas.

861
00:59:28,398 --> 00:59:30,441
If we don't get a reply within 10 minutes,

862
00:59:31,317 --> 00:59:33,820
we can assume North Korea has no intention

863
00:59:34,279 --> 00:59:36,155
of communicating with South Korea.

864
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:43,264
This won't work.
I think we need a different plan.

865
01:00:44,766 --> 01:00:45,767
Where is Secretary Han?

866
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:53,274
Maritime rescue?

867
01:00:53,733 --> 01:00:58,404
Yes, North Korea is asking China
and Russia for a rescue team,

868
01:00:58,488 --> 01:00:59,947
but it doesn't seem to be going well.

869
01:01:00,531 --> 01:01:01,366
I see.

870
01:01:02,617 --> 01:01:04,243
Then it's true

871
01:01:05,995 --> 01:01:08,081
that the submarine sank.

872
01:01:09,248 --> 01:01:10,625
Thank you.

873
01:02:25,783 --> 01:02:27,827
I have something to tell you.

874
01:02:27,910 --> 01:02:29,579
-Yes?
-The submarine...

875
01:02:33,666 --> 01:02:35,543
Secretary Han!

876
01:02:35,626 --> 01:02:36,836
Secretary Han!

877
01:02:36,919 --> 01:02:38,463
-He fainted.
-Guards!

878
01:02:38,546 --> 01:02:40,214
Guards!

879
01:02:40,298 --> 01:02:41,257
Secretary Han.

880
01:02:41,340 --> 01:02:42,341
Wake up.

881
01:02:42,633 --> 01:02:44,385
-Wake up, Secretary Han!
-Emergency!

882
01:02:44,635 --> 01:02:45,678
Get him on my back.

883
01:02:46,929 --> 01:02:48,765
Secretary Han.

884
01:02:50,224 --> 01:02:51,434
Gosh.

885
01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:54,729
Move out of the way.

886
01:02:55,438 --> 01:02:56,314
Secretary Han.

887
01:03:25,426 --> 01:03:26,427
I...

