992
01:16:34,172 --> 01:16:35,340
Secretary Han.

993
01:16:36,466 --> 01:16:37,467
Call President Park.

994
01:16:39,720 --> 01:16:41,013
I need to see him.

995
01:16:46,184 --> 01:16:50,188
Thankfully, your theory
of the submarine sinking

996
01:16:50,939 --> 01:16:51,982
was right.

997
01:16:52,649 --> 01:16:53,900
Thank you.

998
01:16:55,319 --> 01:16:57,112
I never expected you

999
01:16:57,362 --> 01:17:00,407
to take my side
in front of Commander Bell.

1000
01:17:01,199 --> 01:17:04,911
Well, a greenhorn in politics
who has mostly worked

1001
01:17:05,704 --> 01:17:07,581
in academia his whole life

1002
01:17:08,206 --> 01:17:11,251
was about to compromise the alliance
between South Korea and the US.

1003
01:17:12,127 --> 01:17:13,962
I couldn't just sit back
and watch that happen.

1004
01:17:16,131 --> 01:17:18,759
The person in the most danger today
inside the bunker

1005
01:17:19,551 --> 01:17:22,346
wasn’t Commander Bell
or Joint Chiefs of Staff Chairman Lee.

1006
01:17:23,597 --> 01:17:24,723
Acting President

1007
01:17:25,932 --> 01:17:27,351
Park Mu-jin.

1008
01:17:28,185 --> 01:17:29,102
It was you.

1009
01:17:31,271 --> 01:17:32,481
What if

